column4: <content>2 zw/w foto's. Foto 1: Gilles Mostaert. Paesaggio con la Fuga di Lot, 32, 8 x 46 cm. FINCK, Brussels, Nov.-Dec. 1966, N° 9 supposed to be signed GM. R. Finck, Palazzo Strozzi, Florence Oct. 1967; Foto 2: G. MOSTAERT, Landscape with the Flight of Lot, 22,8 x 46 cm. R. FINCK, Brussels, Nov.-Dec. 1966, N° 9, said to be signed GM. R. FINCK, Palazzo Strozzi, Oct. 1967.</content>

<part_of.title>From: Collection 1959 (Summer 1959) Kunsthandel P. de Boer, Amsterdam. Frans Mostaert. [...] The flight of Loth and his daughters from the burning city Sodom, panel 26 x 35 cm. The figures were probably done by his brother Gilles Mostaert.[In bijlage: afbeelding]</part_of.title>
<object.title>Landscape with Sailing Boats and a Burning Town</object.title>
